The United States of America, Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania have issued a joint statement to commemorate the centennial anniversary of Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania's independence. They reaffirm their commitment to principles of democracy, individual liberty, and the rule of law. They also pledge to deepen their collaboration to confront forces threatening their common values and security interests. The statement highlights their commitment to NATO, defense spending, and addressing hybrid threats. They also emphasize the importance of fair and reciprocal trade, energy security, and people-to-people contacts, including student exchanges and support for independent media and journalism.